==English==
===Etymology===
Named for (Hungarian-born) American [[mathematician]] [[w:Paul Halmos|Paul Halmos]] (born 1916) who first used it in [[mathematics]], after seeing it marking the end of articles in [[magazine]]s.
===Noun===
<!-- FIXME: not sure what the plural is -->
[[Category:English nouns]]
# {{mathematics}} The symbol "{{Unicode|&#8718;}}" ([[Unicode]] U+220E, "END OF PROOF") marking the end of a [[proof]].
